article.description: K.J. Jackson registered 11 points as Maryland-Baltimore County beat Albany 62-54 in the America East Conference Tournament quarterfinals on Saturday.
article.headline: UMBC beats Albany 62-54 in America East quarterfinals
article.linkText: UMBC beats Albany 62-54 in America East quarterfinals
article.story: BALTIMORE -- K.J. Jackson registered 11 points as Maryland-Baltimore County beat Albany 62-54 in the America East Conference Tournament quarterfinals on Saturday. Arkel Lamar had 11 points for Maryland-Baltimore County (20-12). Jose Placer added 10 points. Joe Sherburne had eight rebounds for the home team. Malachi De Sousa had 15 points for the Great Danes (12-20). Ahmad Clark added 12 points. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
